you can't fully
realize those things,

02:11:33.780 --> 02:11:35.135
I completely understand that.

02:11:38.340 --> 02:11:42.400
This is going to sound stupid,
but just try your best.

02:11:42.400 --> 02:11:44.890
Because that's why
I have-- creating

02:11:44.890 --> 02:11:47.130
the rubric for this class
was really hard, actually,

02:11:47.130 --> 02:11:49.860
because I knew that all
these constraints were here.

02:11:49.860 --> 02:11:54.000
And so I couldn't raw scale
points, like 10 points

02:11:54.000 --> 02:11:58.070
it's lit correctly, because
that's just unreasonable.

02:11:58.070 --> 02:12:00.490
But what I really
want is the intent

02:12:00.490 --> 02:12:04.600
to be there, the thoughtfulness,
the understanding and self

02:12:04.600 --> 02:12:06.480
awareness of maybe
what's lacking,

02:12:06.480 --> 02:12:08.740
what you'd like to
develop further.

02:12:08.740 --> 02:12:12.860
If you can't-- if a film
location falls through

02:12:12.860 --> 02:12:16.120
at the last minute and you
can't film there, stuff happens.

02:12:16.120 --> 02:12:17.900
I totally understand.

02:12:17.900 --> 02:12:21.570
If you can just maybe write
what you wanted to do instead,

02:12:21.570 --> 02:12:23.300
that's totally fine.

02:12:23.300 --> 02:12:25.388
But--

02:12:25.388 --> 02:12:27.320
AUDIENCE: Same thing
with animations.

02:12:27.320 --> 02:12:31.200
I'm sure some of you have very--
especially with the fractals.

02:12:31.200 --> 02:12:34.180
Zooming in on fractals,
that's a difficult animation

02:12:34.180 --> 02:12:37.430
to accomplish, especially if you
haven't done animation before.

02:12:37.430 --> 02:12:40.480
Think of using still images,
because it's really easy

02:12:40.480 --> 02:12:42.610
to overlay a still
image, or even something

02:12:42.610 --> 02:12:44.280
you draw yourself.

02:12:44.280 --> 02:12:47.461
And it would just kind of like--
what Science Out Loud videos

02:12:47.461 --> 02:12:47.960
do.

02:12:47.960 --> 02:12:50.430
As opposed to making
this really complex,

02:12:50.430 --> 02:12:51.720
like multiple moving pieces.

02:12:51.720 --> 02:12:54.070
The more moving pieces
you have, the harder

02:12:54.070 --> 02:12:58.920
it's going to be to do faster.

02:12:58.920 --> 02:13:02.120
PROFESSOR: We will be around
during class every day.

02:13:02.120 --> 02:13:05.110
So if people want
specific help, like

02:13:05.110 --> 02:13:07.934
Sari's done some
animations herself, too.

02:13:07.934 --> 02:13:09.350
So we can help you
with that stuff

02:13:09.350 --> 02:13:10.920
if you have specific questions.

02:13:10.920 --> 02:13:12.592
But shoot for the best you can.

02:13:12.592 --> 02:13:15.050
Definitely don't be like, well,
I'm going to leave this out

02:13:15.050 --> 02:13:17.216
because I'm just going to
justify to Elizabeth later

02:13:17.216 --> 02:13:19.490
that I couldn't get it.

02:13:19.490 --> 02:13:21.037
Try to do the best you can.

02:13:21.037 --> 02:13:22.870
But I understand the
constraints that you're

02:13:22.870 --> 02:13:25.710
working under for sure.

02:13:25.710 --> 02:13:27.930
So don't stress out about that.

